                <head>No. 356.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 5, 1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>T: I have received your dispatch, No. 5, of the 8th
                    of August last, and have read with much interest the gratifying statement which
                    it contains of the political prospects of a sister republic. The wish of the
                    President for the future of Paraguay, and that the exactions of the governments
                    of Brazil and the Argentine republic in respect to her nationality and territory
                    may be moderate, will be informally communicated to the representatives of those
                    powers.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
